Just FYI, we're now adding `@[deprecated] alias` to things that get deleted. For now, I'm including a `-- deprecated since <date>` comment until we have better support for such a feature within the attribute itself.
I thought the claim was that Yaël requested these names explicitly, but after checking the other PR I see that's not what you meant. I think the names I suggest below are ever so slightly better.

```suggestion
#align equiv.subset_image Equiv.symm_image_subset_iff

@[deprecated] alias subset_image := symm_image_subset_iff -- deprecated since 2024-01-19

```

```suggestion
#align equiv.subset_image' Equiv.subset_symm_image_iff

@[deprecated] alias subset_image' := subset_symm_image_iff -- deprecated since 2024-01-19

```

I understand why you had it in the order you did (for parallelism with `Equiv` versions), but I think this makes more sense here because we don't have any infix notation for `Finset.map`. And I don't think the `_iff` is necessary.
```suggestion
theorem subset_map_symm {t : Finset β} {f : α ≃ β} : s ⊆ t.map f.symm ↔ s.map f ⊆ t := by
```

```suggestion
theorem map_symm_subset {t : Finset β} {f : α ≃ β} : t.map f.symm ⊆ s ↔ t ⊆ s.map f := by
```

```suggestion
protected theorem symm_image_subset {α β} (e : α ≃ β) (s : Set α) (t : Set β) :
```

```suggestion
protected theorem subset_symm_image {α β} (e : α ≃ β) (s : Set α) (t : Set β) :
```
